  "texts": [
    "In contrast, this paper focuses on the core task of unit test generation, aiming to reveal the technical patterns and evolutionary logic unique to this field through deep vertical analysis.In the field of software testing, existing surveys mostly cover broad topics including security testing, general test automation, and debugging [77,112,175].",
    "While these works provide valuable overviews, their breadth limits the depth of exploration into the specific technical details of unit test generation.",
    "Other works focus on a specific technique, such as prompt engineering patterns across the entire SE domain [121], rather than a specific problem domain.The work most closely related to ours is that of [165].",
    "Despite the thematic overlap, there is a fundamental difference in epistemological perspectives between the two.",
    "The former adopts a \"technology-task\" matrix taxonomy, emphasizing comprehensive enumeration."
